# PPDT 2 — Adventure Activities, Organising Steps & Character Positioning

Bhai, ye ek hi complete document hai — saari adventure activities, har ek ki "organise kaise kare" steps, unka Indian association aur famous spots, phir PPDT character-positioning aur best conclusion. Coastal / Mountaineering / General-Aerial — teeno alag-alag grouped. SSB ke liye yaad rakhne layak, action-oriented. Chalo shuru karte hain.

---

## General Expedition Organising Framework (10 Universal Steps)

Koi bhi adventure activity ho — coastal, mountain ya aerial — organise karne ka **basic dimaag ek hi rehta hai**. Yeh 10 steps har activity par fit ho jaate hain. Pehle inhe yaad kar lo, baaki sab activities iska variation hai.

| # | Step | Kya karna hai |
|---|------|---------------|
| 1 | **Aim & Recce** | Objective fix karo (kya, kahan, kab); site ki recce/survey karo. |
| 2 | **Season & Weather** | Best season aur weather window choose karo; risky months avoid karo. |
| 3 | **Permits & Permissions** | Forest/Coast Guard/DGCA/local administration/Inner Line Permit jo zaroori ho lo. |
| 4 | **Participants Screening** | Medical fitness, swimming/age check, consent form aur insurance. |
| 5 | **Qualified Instructors/Guides** | Certified guide/instructor aur safe instructor-to-participant ratio. |
| 6 | **Equipment Check** | Activity-specific gear + safety gear (helmet, PFD, first-aid, rescue kit). |
| 7 | **Logistics** | Transport, ration, fuel, communication aur backup/rescue arrangement. |
| 8 | **Safety Briefing** | Signals, buddy system, emergency drill, do's & don'ts. |
| 9 | **Execution (Supervised)** | Controlled batches, lead-sweep system, regular head-count. |
| 10 | **Debrief & Leave-No-Trace** | Gear collect/rinse, debrief, garbage wapas, log maintain. |

> **Yaad rakhne ka shortcut:** *Aim → Season → Permit → People → Guide → Gear → Logistics → Brief → Do it → Debrief.*

