## Mountaineering / Mountain Activities

Pahaad, rock, ice aur snow wali activities. Common cheez — **altitude, weather aur technical gear**. IMF (Indian Mountaineering Foundation) yahan baar-baar aata hai.

### 1. Mountaineering / High-Altitude Expedition
**Desc:** Bade peaks (6000m+) ko summit karna ice-axe, crampons aur rope ke saath; sabse tough mountain sport.

**Organise kaise kare:**
1. Objective fix — kaunsa peak, kaunsa season (Indian Himalaya May-June ya Sept-Oct best).
2. Team banao + qualified expedition leader/guide + HAP (High Altitude Porters).
3. IMF se peak booking aur expedition permit; foreign peaks ke liye liaison officer rule check.
4. Fitness + acclimatization plan; graded altitude training, medical certificate.
5. Gear: tents, ropes, ice-axe, crampons, oxygen (very high peaks), satellite phone.
6. Logistics: base camp se higher camps load ferrying, ration, fuel.
7. Safety brief: weather forecast, AMS/HAPE/HACE symptoms, evacuation/rescue plan.
8. Summit push schedule with turnaround time rule; Leave-No-Trace wapsi.

| Indian Association | Famous Spots |
|---|---|
| Indian Mountaineering Foundation (IMF), New Delhi — apex body | Mt. Nun & Kun (Ladakh); Stok Kangri (Ladakh); Mt. Shivling & Bhagirathi (Garhwal, UK); Kanchenjunga region (Sikkim) |

### 2. Trekking
**Desc:** Pairon par pahaadon aur valleys me multi-day hiking — sabse popular mountain activity.

**Organise kaise kare:**
1. Route + grade (easy/moderate/difficult) fitness ke hisaab se.
2. Best season/weather window; monsoon me landslide-prone routes avoid.
3. Permits: forest/sanctuary entry + restricted/border areas me Inner Line Permit.
4. Logistics: guide, porter/mule, ration, water purification, first-aid.
5. Day-wise itinerary with acclimatization days (high-altitude treks).
6. Safety brief: buddy system, route marking, emergency contacts, nearest rescue post.
7. Gear: trekking shoes, layered clothing, rain protection, headlamp, poles.
8. Garbage wapas (Leave No Trace) + local logon ka respect.

| Indian Association | Famous Spots |
|---|---|
| IMF (adventure guidelines); state bodies like GMVN (Garhwal Mandal Vikas Nigam) UK treks facilitate karte hain | Roopkund & Valley of Flowers (UK); Hampta Pass & Triund (HP); Kashmir Great Lakes (J&K); Goecha La / Sandakphu (Sikkim-WB) |

### 3. Rock Climbing (Traditional / Natural Rock)
**Desc:** Natural rock faces ko hands aur feet se chadhna rope, harness aur protection gear ke saath.

**Organise kaise kare:**
1. Climbing site + route grade (UIAA/French) level ke hisaab se.
2. Certified instructor/guide; belaying system fix.
3. Land permission (forest/local authority) agar protected area ho.
4. Gear inspect: ropes, harness, helmet, carabiners, quickdraws, nuts/cams (trad).
5. Safety brief: knots (figure-8), belay commands, fall management, anchor checking.
6. Warm-up + route recce; pehle top-rope, phir lead climbing.
7. Spotter + first-aid ready; weather (loose rock after rain) check.
8. Clean climbing — rock damage mat karo, chalk minimal.

