## PPDT Character Positioning & OLQs

PPDT (Picture Perception & Discussion Test) me sirf **4 minute** milte hain story likhne ke liye. Iska matlab — kuch cheezein dimaag me PEHLE se ready honi chahiye.

### 1. Hero (Main Character) ko STRONG Position do

Picture dekhte hi ek character ko hero banao aur usko **clearly define** karo. Examiner ko 2 second me samajh aana chahiye ki leader kaun hai.

**4 cheezein hamesha do — Naam, Umar, Role, Leadership:**

| Element | Kaise karna hai | Example |
|---|---|---|
| **Naam** | Chhota, simple, positive naam | "Rahul", "Arjun", "Vikram" |
| **Umar** | Situation ke hisaab se realistic | "22-saal ka", "25-saal ka" |
| **Role** | Group me uska kaam/position | "NCC cadet", "trek leader", "engineering student aur team captain" |
| **Leadership** | Wo decision lene wala / aage badhne wala | "group ka leader hone ke naate Arjun ne…" |

**Strong opening line ka formula:** *Naam + Umar + Role + wo kya kar raha tha*

> **Example:** "Arjun, ek 24-saal ka energetic NCC cadet aur apni 6-logon ki trekking team ka leader, Himachal ke ek mushkil pahaadi route par expedition par nikla tha."

Ek hi line me naam, umar, role, leadership aur situation — sab clear. Yahi STRONG positioning hai.

**Galti se bachna:** "Wo ladka", "ek aadmi", "kuch log" — aise vague mat likho. Hero ka naam turant do.

### 2. OLQs — 4 Factors mein grouped (4-5 naturally surface karo)

SSB 15 OLQs dekhta hai, jo **4 factors** me bante hain. Poora list ratne ki zaroorat nahi — har factor se 1-2 quality story me **action ke through dikhao** (likh ke mat batao "Arjun brave tha", balki uska brave kaam dikhao).

**Factor 1 — Planning & Organizing (Dimaag):** Effective Intelligence, Reasoning Ability, Organizing Ability, Power of Expression.
**Factor 2 — Social Adjustment (Logon ke saath):** Social Adaptability, Cooperation, Sense of Responsibility.
**Factor 3 — Social Effectiveness (Leadership):** Initiative, Self-Confidence, Speed of Decision, Ability to Influence the Group, Liveliness.
**Factor 4 — Dynamic / Action (Himmat):** Determination, Courage, Stamina.

**Naturally surface karne ka trick — 1 quality = 1 chhota action:**

| OLQ | Story mein action |
|---|---|
| Initiative | "Sabse pehle Arjun aage badha aur charge liya" |
| Speed of Decision | "Bina time waste kiye usne turant decide kiya ki…" |
| Courage + Stamina | "Theek se rope baandh kar wo khud neeche utra aur ghayal saathi ko upar khincha" |
| Cooperation | "Usne baaki team ko bhi alag-alag kaam baant diye" |
| Determination | "Mushkil ke bawajood usne team ko hausla diya ki hum yeh kar sakte hain" |

5 OLQs ho gaye — bina ek baar bhi "OLQ" ka naam liye. **Show, don't tell.**

### 3. Ideal Story Flow (5 steps)

```
Situation → Problem → Hero ka Plan/Action → Team Effort → Positive Result
```

**Full example (adventure/expedition):**
1. **Situation:** "Arjun, 24-saal ka NCC cadet, apni 6-member team ke saath Himachal me high-altitude trek par tha."
2. **Problem:** "Achanak mausam kharab hua, ek saathi phisal kar chot kha gaya aur raasta dhundla pad gaya."
3. **Plan/Action:** "Arjun ne turant decide kiya — pehle ghayal saathi ko first-aid diya, phir map aur compass se safe shelter ka raasta dhoondha."
4. **Team Effort:** "Usne team ko do groups me baanta — ek ghayal ko sambhalne, doosra raasta clear karne. Sab ne mil kar kaam kiya."
5. **Positive Result:** "Shaam tak puri team safe base camp pahunch gayi, ghayal saathi bhi theek tha, aur expedition successfully complete hua."

Notice: Hero akela hero nahi banta — wo **team ko saath le kar** result laata hai. SSB ko yahi chahiye (lone-wolf hero nahi, **team leader hero**).

