## Best Conclusion Templates

Conclusion sabse important hai — yahi last impression hai. Ek achhi closing line me **3 cheezein** honi chahiye:
**(a) Result + (b) Appreciation/recognition + (c) Learning/aage ka kaam.**

### 4 Reusable Closing-Line Templates

**Template 1 — Result + Appreciation:**
> "Puri team safely apni manzil par pahunch gayi, aur sabne Arjun ke shaant dimaag aur leadership ki taarif ki."

**Template 2 — Result + Learning:**
> "Mission successfully poora hua, aur is anubhav se team ne seekha ki ekjut ho kar har mushkil aasaan ho jaati hai."

**Template 3 — Result + Future contribution (best for expedition):**
> "Arjun ki samajhdari se sab surakshit lautey, aur usne aage aise aur bhi adventure camps lead karne ka faisla kiya."

**Template 4 — Result + Recognition + Inspiration:**
> "Kaam time se poora hua, seniors ne Arjun ki sarahna ki, aur uski team uske liye ek misaal (role model) ban gayi."

**All-rounder favourite (result + appreciation + learning, ek hi line me):**
> "Arjun ki turant leadership se team safe nikal aayi, sabne uski taarif ki, aur is experience ne unhe future ke liye aur bhi confident bana diya."

### Conclusion ke DO's
1. **Hamesha positive aur successful end karo** — result achha hona chahiye (team safe, kaam poora, sab khush).
2. **Hero ko credit + team ka contribution dono dikhao** — "Arjun ki leadership se *team* ne yeh kiya."

### Conclusion ke DON'Ts
1. **Negative / adhura end mat karo** — koi mar gaya, mission fail, "pata nahi kya hua" — bilkul nahi. SSB positive, solution-oriented soch dekhta hai.
2. **Conclusion rushed/flat mat chhodo** — "…aur sab theek ho gaya." jaisi line mat likho. Hamesha proper, complete, result-wali line do.

